article.headline: Miami 74, Tulane 54
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Dwayne Collins had 23 points and 14 rebounds as Miami overpowered Tulane 74-54 Thursday in the first round of the Charleston Classic. Collins made all eight of his shots from the field, and eight of his rebounds came on the offensive end. The Hurricanes (3-0) broke away in the second half with a 19-4 run. They advanced to play the Penn State-UNC Wilmington winner. Kris Richard scored 13 points for Tulane (0-2).
